<p>

<table width="600" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="5"><tr><td nowrap valign="top">
<strong>Denomination</strong></td><td nowrap valign="top">
(IAjapan: Internet Association Japan)
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top">
<strong>Foundation</strong></td><td valign="top">
Legally permitted in July 1, 2001
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top">
<strong>Mission</strong></td><td valign="top">
"Establishment of the future society on the Internet":<br>Aiming to establish an Advanced Information Society and to contribute both to Japanese economic growth and improved human life by promoting the growth of the Internet
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
<strong>Authorities</strong></td><td valign="top">
<a href = "http://www.soumu.go.jp/english/">Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications (MIC)</a> and <a href = "http://www.meti.go.jp/english/">Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry (METI)</a>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top">
<strong>Scope</strong></td><td valign="top">
As a new association, IAjapan has inherited its activities from the Internet Association of Japan (IAJ) and <a href = "http://www.enc.or.jp/eindex.html">the Electronic Network Consortium (ENC)</a>, IAjapan is planning to conduct more extensive activities than before.
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top">

<strong>Activity</strong></td><td valign="top">
<ul>
<li>Holding seminars regarding the latest Internet technologies and trends <br>
<li>Deployment of filtering software and development/operation of rating systems<br>
<li>Various working group activities<br>
<li>Training human resources<br>
<li>Development and demonstration regarding Internet technologies<br>
<li>Promoting the standardization of Internet technologies<br>
<li>Coordinating with other standard bodies regarding Internet technologies<br>
<li>Research on Internet trends<br>

<li><a href = "http://www.iajapan.org/hotline/">Secretariat of Internet Hotline Expert Network</a><br>
<li>Cooperation with international Internet organizations such as<br>
W3C, IETF, ISOC, ICANN, APIA, APNG
</ul>
</td></tr>
</table>


<table CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="3">
<tr><td colspan="3">
<strong>History</strong></td>
<tr><td  nowrap>
March 1991</td>
<td valign="top" nowrap>
Established Japan Networking Association (JNA)
</td><td rowspan="10"></td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
April 1992</td><td valign="top" nowrap>
Launched Electronic Network Consortium (ENC)
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
December 1993</td><td valign="top" nowrap>
Established Internet Association of Japan (IAJ)
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
September 1996 </td><td valign="top" nowrap>
Established Java Conference (Java-Conf)
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
June 2000</td><td valign="top" nowrap>
Japan Networking Association (JNA) and Java Conference (Java-Conf) <br>were merged after they were absorbed into the Internet Association of Japan (IAJ)
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
August 2000</td><td valign="top" nowrap>
Started consideration of incorporation at "The New Incorporated <br>Association Preliminary Committee"
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
October 2000</td><td valign="top" nowrap>
Started legitimate consideration of incorporation at "New Incorporated Association<br> Review Committee", "Project review working group"and "Secretariat meeting"
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
March 2001</td><td valign="top" nowrap>
Established Internet Association Japan (IAjapan)
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
April 2001</td><td valign="top" nowrap>
Electronic Network Consortium (ENC) and Internet Association <br>of Japan (IAJ) were consolidated as IAjapan
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" nowrap>
July 2001</td><td valign="top" nowrap>
Legally permitted by Ministry of Public Management, Home Affairs, <br>Posts and Telecommunications, and Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry
</td></tr>
</table>
